pulses.name: 20240802 Most Active Threat Indicators
pulses.description:
02 Aug 2024 : Most Active Threat Indicators
#Cybersecurity #Cyberattack #RCE #Botnet #IOC

The majority of attacks are originating from the United States, followed by China and India. The most common types of attacks include command injection vulnerabilities in various routers and devices, such as LB-LINK, NETGEAR DGN1000, and GPON routers. These attacks allow attackers to execute arbitrary commands on the vulnerable systems, potentially leading to further compromise and misuse of the affected devices. To mitigate these threats, it is crucial for organizations and individuals to ensure that their network devices are kept up-to-date with the latest security patches and that strong access control measures are implemented to prevent unauthorized access.
